<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="utf-8" />
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
  <title>{{ title }}</title>

  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/assets/styles.css" />
</head>

<body>

  <main class="page">

    <div class="title">
      {{ title }}
    </div>

    <div class="text">
      {{ content | safe }}
    </div>

    <div class="links">
      <a href="/changelog/">
        <span class="link-title">Changelog</span>
        <span class="link-desc">
          A complete history of updates, improvements, and fixes across versions so you can track what has changed over time.
        </span>
      </a>

      <a href="/projectMan/">
        <span class="link-title">Project Management</span>
        <span class="link-desc">
          Covers how projects are planned, organized, and executed, including workflows, task structure, and collaboration practices.
        </span>
      </a>

      <a href="/dep-dev/">
        <span class="link-title">Design Pattern</span>
        <span class="link-desc">
          Explains reusable design solutions and architectural patterns used to solve common problems in a consistent way.
        </span>
      </a>

      <a href="/dep-dev/">
        <span class="link-title">Development</span>
        <span class="link-desc">
          Documents coding standards, development workflows, and best practices to ensure consistency and maintainability.
        </span>
      </a>

      <a href="/dep-dev/">
        <span class="link-title">Navigation Flow</span>
        <span class="link-desc">
          Describes how users move through the application, including structure, hierarchy, and interaction flow between pages.
        </span>
      </a>

      <a href="/maintainer/">
        <span class="link-title">Maintainer</span>
        <span class="link-desc">
          Defines the responsibilities, processes, and guidelines for maintaining the project over time, including updates and reviews.
        </span>
      </a>
    </div>

    <div class="sub-trees">
      <a href="/atty/">
        <span class="link-title">Accessibility</span>
        <span class="link-desc">
          Understand what accessibility means in web development and why it matters, then learn how to correctly use ARIA to enhance usability without breaking native behavior.
        </span>
      </a>

      <a href="/schema/">
        <span class="link-title">Schema</span>
        <span class="link-desc">
          A reference section for JSON-LD structured data used throughout the site, detailing how entities, pages, and relationships are modeled to form a consistent and scalable knowledge graph.
        </span>
      </a>
    </div>

  </main>

</body>
</html>